  "prompt": "Is six hours of sleep enough for a 10-year-old?",
  "response": "No, six hours of sleep is generally not enough for a 10-year-old. Children in this age group typically need about 9-12 hours of sleep per night to support their physical and mental development. Insufficient sleep can lead to issues such as difficulty concentrating, mood swings, and overall poor health. It\u2019s important for a 10-year-old to get adequate sleep to ensure they are well-rested and able to function optimally during the day.",
